veman |first2=L.S. |last2=Beresford |title=If you’re so smart, why aren’t you the boss? Explaining the persistent vertical gender gap in management |journal=[[The Annals of the American Academy of Political and Social Science]] |volume=639 |year=2012 |pages=114–30 |doi=10.1177/0002716211418443 |ref = harv}} *{{cite journal |ref=harv |last=Mincer |first=J. |title=Human Capital and Economic Growth |journal=NBER Working Paper |issue=802 |year=1891}} *{{cite journal |ref=harv |last1=Tilcsik |first1=A. |last2=Anteby |first2=M. |last3=Knight |first3=C. |title=Concealable Stigma and Occupational Segregation: Toward a Theory of Gay and Lesbian Occupations |journal=[[Administrative Science Quarterly]] |volume=60 |issue=3 |year=2015 |pages=446–481 | url=https://tspace.library.utoronto.ca/bitstream/1807/67780/1/asq2015.pdf}} *{{cite journal |ref=harv |last=Watts |first=M.J. |title=On the Conceptualisation and Measurement of Horizontal and Vertical Occupational Gender Segregation |journal=European Sociological Review |volume=21 |year=2005 |pages=481–488 |doi=10.1093/esr/jci034}} *{{cite book |ref=harv |last=Weeden |first=K. |title=Occupational Segregation |work=[[Blackwell Encyclopedia of Sociology]] |editor=Ritzer, George |publisher=[[Blackwell Publishing]] |year=2007}} <!-- {{sfn|Weeden, Kim|2007}} --> **Online: {{cite web |title=Blackwell Reference Online |date=31 March 2008 |url=http://www.blackwellreference.com/subscriber/tocnode?id=g9781405124331_chunk_g978140512433121_ss1-4}}
